*edit* ok... didnt wanna leave a post just like that<br>
<br>
im in a mid to high level guild / alliance...  more haste for me means more aggro when i dont want it.<br>
<br>
but, more AC, more WIS espcially... means some other things i can do,.... more mana give me some more casts of Wave Of Healing, a well placed stun, etc etc....<br>
<br>
last time i was in ToV, we had a cleric shortage the second day, and i spent more time healing AE damage than i did swinging.<br>
<br>
if you wanna solo, get more haste.  If you are always the main assist... get more haste..<br>
<br>
if you are there to BE an assist, read: help with healing and other things that do not involve haste or melee damage, go more with other stats.<br>
<br>
stats arent all, i never said that.  but neither is haste and ac....  you have to have a good balance of the three to have a sucessful character.  If you have 1800ac, but crap hps and no haste, you pretty much suck.... if you have 80% item haste, but no ac, and crap hps... you suck again (welcome to the world of the ranger, aggro when you dont want it). If you have 4000 mana, but crap everything else, guess what.. you suck again....<br>
<br>
i try to speard myself out... its the way i play.  If you want to focus totally on melee, its my opnion you should play a warrior, because a paladin is so much more diverse than a warrior.<br>
